│ ### 1. Understanding the Issue                                                             │
│                                                                                            │
│ The `vector-combine` pass is attempting to fold a sequence of `extractelement` and         │
│ `insertelement` instructions into a single `shufflevector` instruction. This optimization  │
│ is beneficial as a single shuffle is often cheaper than the extract/insert pair. The issue │
│ arises when the pass tries to calculate the cost of the potential new shuffle. The cost    │
│ analysis, performed by the Target Transform Info (TTI), receives an invalid shuffle mask,  │
│ which leads to an assertion failure.                                                       │
│                                                                                            │
│ ### 2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log                                                               │
│                                                                                            │
│ The `opt` log shows that the `vector-combine` pass is visiting the instructions in the     │
│ `test` function. The crash occurs when visiting the `insertelement` instruction: `%ins =   │
